--- !u!114 &447340142
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 447340140}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 12f64560c0966fb40adf1872cf70c6e4, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  currentDialogueLine: 0
  amountOfDialogueLines: 0
  dialogueLines:
  - TimeBeforeStarting to press the start button?
  - Awfully bold of you to be this tardy on your first day.
  - Anyways, before we talk any further, what was your name again?
  - I mean, I know your name is UserName, but I just wanna make sure.
  - InputField
  - InputtedName?
  - ...
  - Not gonna lie, that's pretty cringe. I'm just gonna call you "Pikachu".
  - That cool with you?
  - ButtonPrompt
  - Glad to hear we can cooperate together, Pikachu.
  - Glad to hear we can cooperate together, Pikachu.
  - Anyways, let's move on from that now and get to what you're here for today. Becoming
    a Package Creature User.
  - As you know, The Developer made this world using Packages. Everything in our
    world is comprised of at least one of these.
  - In recent years we found a way to actually use these Packages to create creatures,
    hence why we call them Package Creatures.
  - Usually no one would care (me included), but these things are actually kinda
    handy.
  - As they're made from a particular Package they have abilities taken from it,
    which we can use for solving the worlds less larger problems.
  - Car crashes, drug busts, grabbing a child's balloon from a tree branch and so
    on. Which is what you'll be doing...
  - ...in the future that is. I'd be insane to let a newbie like you on the field
    immeditely. I got a reputation y'know?
  - You'll be going through my personal newbie training scenario to learn the ropes.
  - As you're still green, I'm only giving you access to ONE Package Creature. These
    are dangerous I don't want another dead body on my hands.
  - Inpup would probably be the safest choice for you. When you get onto the ground
    you'll find a sign which will give you instructions for how to get them.
  - Anyways, that pretty much does it. Just one more thing I need to do now.
  - Smile! PlayerProfilePicture
  - Hope you like your profile picture.
  - Photoshoots are expensive so there are no retakes.
  dialogueText: {fileID: 2054974452}
  nameText: {fileID: 0}
  timeBtwnChars: 0.01
